{"word":"κακόνυμφος","slug":"κακόνυμφος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κακόνυμφος</b></el> <el>(κᾰκό-νυμφος, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:νύμφη'><el>νύμφη</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>ill-married, of unhappy wedlock</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a> <i>an ill</i> or <i>unhappy bridegroom</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}